          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Indexes",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The primary key index ("
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "PK_MenuItemPermission",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ") is clustered, which is optimal for range queries and ensures efficient retrieval of records by "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "MenuItemPermissionSeqID",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Query Performance",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Given the table's role in access control, queries will involve joins with the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "MenuItem",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "aspnet_Roles",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " tables. Ensuring these tables are also indexed appropriately will enhance performance."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Scalability",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": As the number of roles and menu items grows, the table become large. Monitoring query performance and considering additional indexes on "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "MenuItemSeqID",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "RoleID",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " be beneficial."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
